EZ Energy Surges Most Since September on Oil, Gas Rights Talks

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-08-04T08:11:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/ez-energy-surges-most-since-september-on-oil-gas-rights-talks.html
EZ Energy Ltd. (EZ)  soared the most in 11
months after the operator of gas stations and convenience stores
said it’s  in talks  to acquire 10 percent of the partnership
rights to two licenses at the “Gal” oil and gas site.  The shares jumped 20 percent, the most since Sept. 14, to
0.06 shekel at 10:46 a.m. in Tel Aviv, giving the  Ramat Gan ,
Israel-based company a market value of 61.6 million shekels ($18
million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  